Chapter 7: Broader Impact & Future Directions

7.1 Scientific Discovery

The TCA framework can be seen as a model of automated science: an agent that plans experiments to reduce uncertainty about a hypothesis. This connects to self‑driving laboratories and AI‑driven discovery.

7.2 Foundation Models as Priors

Large language models and other foundation models can serve as rich priors over world models. ECS would then perform active data acquisition to refine these priors, combining generative AI with epistemic control.

7.3 Human‑AI Collaboration

The LogPool fusion naturally extends to human‑robot teams: a human expert’s belief can be combined with the robot’s belief using entropy‑based weights, allowing the system to respect human confidence while leveraging machine perception.

7.4 Trustworthy Autonomy

The exponential convergence guarantee and safety constraints directly address requirements for safety‑critical systems outlined in NASA/ESA guidelines. This positions TCA as a foundational contribution to the emerging field of epistemic autonomy.

